Latvia Won’t See Balanced Budget Before ’15, Premier Tells Avize

-- B y   A a r o n   E g l i t i s
-- 
2011-03-01T07:38:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/latvia-won-t-see-balanced-budget-before-15-premier-tells-avize.html
Latvia won’t see a balanced budget
before 2015, a year after it plans to adopt the euro, Prime
Minister Valdis Dombrovskis said, according to  Latvijas Avize .  The Baltic country has implemented austerity measures worth
about 16 percent of gross domestic product since 2008 and plans
for a budget deficit of 5.4 percent this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aaron Eglitis in Riga at 
 aeglitis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor for this story:
Willy Morris at   wmorris@bloomberg.net  